statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from `factories` inner join `user_franchise` on `factories`.`id` = `user_franchise`.`factory_id` inner join `franchises` on `user_franchise`.`franchise_id` = `franchises`.`id` inner join `cities` on `franchises`.`city_id` = `cities`.`id` where `user_franchise`.`user_id` is null and `user_franchise`.`factory_id` is not null and `user_franchise`.`reception_id` is null and `factories`.`deleted` = 0 and `user_franchise`.`franchise_id` = 1

select `factories`.`id` as `id`, `franchises`.`name` as `name`, CONCAT(cities.name, ', ', factories.address) as address, IFNULL(factories.name, 'нет') as address_name, `factories`.`phone` as `phone` from `factories` inner join `user_franchise` on `factories`.`id` = `user_franchise`.`factory_id` inner join `franchises` on `user_franchise`.`franchise_id` = `franchises`.`id` inner join `cities` on `franchises`.`city_id` = `cities`.`id` where `user_franchise`.`user_id` is null and `user_franchise`.`factory_id` is not null and `user_franchise`.`reception_id` is null and `factories`.`deleted` = 0 and `user_franchise`.`franchise_id` = 1 order by `factories`.`created_at` desc limit 10 offset 0
select CONCAT(link, '.index') as link, `name`, `icon` from `links` order by `order_by` asc
